data.title: Ok cafe
data.text:
The Federal Cafe is a small deli style cafe located on the first floor in the US District Court building in downtown Minneapolis.

It's not that busy of a place, since it's not on the skyway, and is kind of tucked away.

It has a small salad bar and a sandwich/burger counter.  There is only one cash register.

They have a big dining room with a lot of tables.  It faces south so it bright and cheery.

I had the Beer cheese soup off of the salad bar, and it was very good.

data.title: Tasty and quick
data.text: Great burgers and fast service. Food is made fresh while you wait. Convenient location as well. Can't beat that!
